@node "MoreNodeEditI" "More Node Edit I"


                       @{b}SystemEditor: More Node Edit I Window
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure more Node dependant options.
What you configure here is local and only available for the current Node.

           @{"      NamesNotAllowed       " link "SEMNodeINamesNotAllowed"} @{"          Rip CON           " link "SEMNodeIRipCON"}
           @{"         NET NodeID         " link "SEMNodeINETNodeID"} @{"       Conf. Preset         " link "SEMNodeIConfPreset"}
           @{"         NewUserKey         " link "SEMNodeINewUserKey"} @{"      BatchStackSize        " link "SEMNodeIBatchStackSize"}
           @{"      RipSuffix define      " link "SEMNodeIRipSuffixdefine"} @{"      Batch Priority        " link "SEMNodeIBatchPriority"}
           @{"         1. Timeout         " link "SEMNodeI1Timeout"} @{"    Async. Startbatches     " link "SEMNodeIAsyncStartbatches"}
           @{"         2. Timeout         " link "SEMNodeI2Timeout"} @{"    Async. Logonbatches     " link "SEMNodeIAsyncLogonbatches"}
           @{"        DoorTimeOut         " link "SEMNodeIDoorTimeOut"} @{"    Async. Logoffbatches    " link "SEMNodeIAsyncLogoffbatches"}
           @{"          BaudRate          " link "SEMNodeIBaudRate"} @{"   Async. ShutDownbatches   " link "SEMNodeIAsyncShutDownbatches"}
           @{"         StartTime          " link "SEMNodeIStartTime"} @{"     Display zero bytes     " link "SEMNodeIDisplayzerobytes"}
           @{"          EndTime           " link "SEMNodeIEndTime"} @{"      Shanghai Windows      " link "SEMNodeIShanghaiWindows"}
           @{"            SAVE            " link "SEMNodeISAVE"} @{"    Relative Conferences    " link "SEMNodeIRelativeConferences"}
           @{"           DELETE           " link "SEMNodeIDELETE"} @{"        NoExtSysOpLg        " link "SEMNodeINoExtSysOpLg"}
           @{"   If BaudTime not found    " link "SEMNodeIIfBaudTimenotfound"} @{"        Allow Hydra         " link "SEMNodeIAllowHydra"}
           @{" Display Passwords to SysOp " link "SEMNodeIDisplayPasswordstoSysOp"} @{"       Allow RIP Gfx        " link "SEMNodeIAllowRIPGfx"}
           @{"      Internal UserEd       " link "SEMNodeIInternalUserEd"} @{"         Default OH         " link "SEMNodeIDefaultOH"}
           @{"          NewUser           " link "SEMNodeINewUser"} @{"        MinUsNaChars        " link "SEMNodeIMinUsNaChars"}
           @{"        Allow SModem        " link "SEMNodeIAllowSModem"} @{"        MinUsPWChars        " link "SEMNodeIMinUsPWChars"}
           @{"        ANSI Prompt         " link "SEMNodeIANSIPrompt"} @{"     Free Download Node     " link "SEMNodeIFreeDownloadNode"}

                         @{"            BACK            " link "SEMNodeIBACK"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINamesNotAllowed" "NamesNotAllowed"


                @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NamesNotAllowed
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here where the file 'NamesNotAllowed.txt' can be found.
Normally '<BBSLocation>:NamesNotAllowed.txt'.

Note: Place into this text file under the following names: - SYSOP
                                                           - ALL
                                                           - EALL
                                                           - UEALL

...and others like 'fuck' etc etc ...

These names cannot be used as usernames.

The four names above are reserved for FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINETNodeID" "NET NodeID"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NET NodeID
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The id if you are running a network.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeINewUserKey" "NewUserKey"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): NewUserKey
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the NewUserKey.

Note: Define a special keyword for example 'GUEST' if you have the gadget
      @{"NewUser" link "SEMNodeINewUser"} set to @{"NewUserKey Wait" link "SEMNodeINewUser"}.

      In combination with @{"NewUser" link "SEMNodeINewUser"} set to @{"NewUserKey Wait" link "SEMNodeINewUser"} your Node reacts
      like as if @{"NewUser" link "SEMNodeINewUser"} would be set to @{"No NewUser" link "SEMNodeINewUser"}.

      Only if a user knows your NewUserKey and types it correctly at the
      UserNamePrompt (instead of a username) the user will be able to begin
      as a newuser.

Note: If a 'NewUserKey' is set, it will automatically be added by MainPart
      into the NamesNotAllowed list so you needn't to put it into the
      @{"NamesNotAllowed.txt" link "SEMNodeINamesNotAllowed"} by hand.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIRipSuffixdefine" "RipSuffix define"


                @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): RipSuffix define
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the suffix of RIP files.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeI1Timeout" "1. Timeout"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): 1. Timeout
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the first timeout. On first timeout the Node sends a beep and
starts the second timeout.

Default: 180 seconds.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeI2Timeout" "2. Timeout"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): 2. Timeout
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the second timeout. If also the second timeout is reached,
the user will be kicked off, and the Node resets for the next caller.

Default: 60 seconds.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMNodeIDoorTimeOut" "DoorTimeOut"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (More Node Edit I): DoorTimeOut
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Define here the timout a door can have until nothing happens.

Default 120 seconds.

Note: It's dependant on the door to react correctly on doorport results to
      quit immediatly.

@endnode

