                @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): ModemOffHook
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Modem off hook string, normally 'ATM0H1'.

Note: ~ inserts a 1/2 - 1 second pause.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SESeMoScNumOfRings" "Number of rings"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Serial/Modem/Screen): Number of rings
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Number of rings indicates how many rings have to come in till the Node
let's the Modem answer.

On every ring a timer will be started for 10 seconds. After 10 seconds
the ringcounter will be reseted and the Node resets. On the final ring
the timer will be set to 30 seconds (after the modem answer string has
been send) to wait for the connect 30 seconds long (just as it was
implemented before).

Default is 1.

@endnode

