@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMoreConf" "More Conferences"


                         @{b}SystemEditor: More Conferences
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure more conference dependant options.
What you configure here is local and only available for the current conf.

                          @{"    Conference Password     " link "SEMoCoCnfPassword"}
                          @{" ConfPW Mail/File scan skip " link "SEMoCoConfPWMFScSk"}

                          @{"            BACK            " link "SEMoCoBACK"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMoCoCnfPassword" "Conference Password"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): Conference Password
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can enter a password for joining a conference.

If no password is set the password check is disabled, entering here
a passowrd enables the password check on joining this Conference.

Only users which are knowing the correct password will be able join
this Conference.

On removing the password the Conference can be joined again without
any security password check.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMoCoConfPWMFScSk" "ConfPW Mail/File scan skip"


             @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): ConfPW Mail/File scan skip
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

On activating this gadget and if a @{"Conference Password" link "SEMoCoCnfPassword"} is set the mail/file
scanner won't scan this Conference any longer for new mails and files.

In this case the scanner will tell the user that scanning is not possible
on this Conference.

Only if a user joins successfully the Conference by hand the mails and files
will be scanned.

An exception will be made also if a user is logging on and enters
successfully on rejoining a Conference the password.
In this case the scanner will also scan this Conference, but no other
Conference with a password set.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEMoCoBACK" "BACK"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Conferences): BACK
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Close this window and go back into the Conferences window of the SystemEditor.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "AccessSecure" "Access / Secure"


                         @{b}SystemEditor: Access / Secure
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can go to one of the following windows:

                              @{"      Levels       " link "Levels" 0}
                              @{" Conference Access " link "ConferenceAccess" 0}
                              @{"     Presets       " link "Presets" 0}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Levels" "Levels"


                             @{b}SystemEditor: Levels
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure all level dependant options.
The options configured for a level will be used to define what a user is
able to do in the bbs and what not.

If a user comes into the bbs and no level configfile exists for the user
the next lower one will be used.

On a user logon the node first tries to find a level with the user number
which will look like: "FAME:Settings/Access/Levels/<usernumber>.dat".
If this is not found the node tries to find a level with the username
which will look like: "FAME:Settings/Access/Levels/<username>.dat".
If this also can't be found the node tries to find a level with the users
level which will look like:
"FAME:Settings/Access/Levels/Level<userlevel>.dat".
If this also can't be find the node tries to load the next lower one.
If nothing can be found the node will set limited default values.

               @{"    (R)ead Messages    " link "SELevelReadMessages"} @{"      Relogin (RL)     " link "SELevelRelogin"}
               @{"    (E)nter Message    " link "SELevelEnterMessage"} @{"     Upload Status     " link "SELevelUploadStatus"}
               @{"  (C)omment to SysOp   " link "SELevelCommenttoSysOp"} @{" Public Message Files  " link "SELevelPublicMessageFiles"}
               @{"    Page SysOp (O)     " link "SELevelPageSysOp"} @{" Private Message Files " link "SELevelPrivateMessageFiles"}
               @{"      (ZOOM) Mail      " link "SELevelZoomMail"} @{"      Attach File      " link "SELevelAttachFile"}
               @{"   Read (B)ulletins    " link "SELevelReadBulletins"} @{"     MCI Messages      " link "SELevelMCIMessages"}
               @{"    (WHO) is Online    " link "SELevelWHOisOnline"} @{"      Break Chat       " link "SELevelBreakChat"}
               @{"     User (S)tatus     " link "SELevelUserStatus"} @{"     Overide Chat      " link "SELevelOverideChat"}
               @{"  (Z)ippy Text Search  " link "SELevelZippyTextSearch"} @{"     Overide Time      " link "SELevelOverideTime"}
               @{"   (J)oin Conference   " link "SELevelJoinConference"} @{"     EAll Messages     " link "SELevelEAllMessages"}
               @{"    (F)ile Listing     " link "SELevelFileListing"} @{"     Edit Dirs (5)     " link "SELevelEditDirs"}
               @{"      (N)ew Files      " link "SELevelNewFiles"} @{"     Edit Files (6)    " link "SELevelEditFiles"}
               @{"       (U)pload        " link "SELevelUpload"} @{"    Delete Messages    " link "SELevelDeleteMessages"}
               @{"      (D)ownload       " link "SELevelDownload"} @{"  Account Editing (1)  " link "SELevelAccountEditing"}
               @{"     (V)iew Files      " link "SELevelViewFiles"} @{"    SysOp Commands     " link "SELevelSysOpCommands"}
               @{"     Free Resuming     " link "SELevelFreeResuming"} @{"       Shell (0)       " link "SELevelShell"}
               @{"    GlobalUD (UG/DG)   " link "SELevelGlobalUD"} @{"      SysOp Read       " link "SELevelSysOpRead"}
               @{" Edit User Account (W) " link "SELevelEditUserAccount"} @{"    SysOp View (VS)    " link "SELevelSysOpView"}
               @{"     Edit Password     " link "SELevelEditPassword"} @{"  SysOp Download (DS)  " link "SELevelSysOpDownload"}
               @{"  Edit User Location   " link "SELevelEditUserLocation"} @{"   Overide Defaults    " link "SELevelOverideDefaults"}
               @{" Edit User City/State  " link "SELevelEditUserCityState"} @{"       Max Pages       " link "SELevelMaxPages"}
               @{"     Edit Username     " link "SELevelEditUsername"} @{"     Max Relogins      " link "SELevelMaxRelogins"}
               @{"   Edit Phonenumber    " link "SELevelEditPhonenumber"}

               @{"         Level         " link "SELevelLevel"} @{"          255          " link "SELevel255"}
               @{"        SELECT         " link "SELevelSELECT"} @{"           <           " link "SELevelLeft"}
               @{"           1           " link "SELevel1"} @{"           >           " link "SELevelRight"}
               @{"          10           " link "SELevel10"} @{"      More Levels      " link "MoreLevels"}
               @{"          50           " link "SELevel50"} @{"         BACK          " link "SELevelBACK"}
               @{"          100          " link "SELevel100"} @{"         SAVE          " link "SELevelSAVE"}
