@REM==============================================================================

@node "ConferenceAccess" "Conference Access"


                        @{b}SystemEditor: Conference Access
                       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure the conference access for a user or special
types/groups of users.

On a user logon the node first tries to find a conference access file
with the users conference access selected for the user via preset or by
hand in the user editor on validating the user.
This one will look like: "FAME:Settings/Access/Conferences/<user access>.dat".
If this is not found the node tries to find a conference access file
with the username which will look like:
"FAME:Settings/Access/Conferences/<username>.dat".
If this also can't be found the node tries to find a conference access file
with the user number which will look like:
"FAME:Settings/Access/Conferences/<usernumber>.dat".

If nothing can be found the node will set the conference to conference 1 only.

                              @{" Conference Alias " link "SEConfXSConferenceAlias"}
                              @{"  Auto Selection  " link "SEConfXSAutoSelection"}
                              @{"       1-xxx      " link "SEConfXS1xxx"}

                              @{"      Bank<x>     " link "SEConfXSBankx"}
                              @{"        NEW       " link "SEConfXSNEW"}
                              @{"      DELETE      " link "SEConfXSDELETE"}
                              @{"       BACK       " link "SEConfXSBACK"}
                              @{"       SAVE       " link "SEConfXSSAVE"}
                              @{"     SAVE+USE     " link "SEConfXSSAVEUSE"}
                              @{"        USE       " link "SEConfXSUSE"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfXSConferenceAlias" "Conference Alias"


               @{b}SystemEditor (Conference Access): Conference Alias
              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The conference alias is the Name of this access, for example: 'SysOp' or
'XXX__XX___X_'. It can also be a user number or name like: '1'
or 'Testuser'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfXSAutoSelection" "Auto Selection"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Conference Access): Auto Selection
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

If Auto Selection is on @{"Conference Aliases" link "SEConfXSConferenceAlias"} where one or more 'X' can be
found in the name will be used to set the gadgets 1-xxx to checked state on
the equal position in the string, for example:
'XXX__XX___X_' means: 1,2,3,6,7 and 11 on, rest off.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEConfXS1xxx" "1-xxx"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Conference Access): 1-xxx
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The conference number. Checked means conference access allowed, else not.

@endnode

