@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoorsDoorConfig" "Door Config"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Doors): Door Config
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure (FIM) doors to make them available to the BBS as
DoorConfig doors. You can sort them in a list and the Node (MainPart) will
use the sorted list to display them in the same way to the user.

DoorConfig doors are either extra doors or the door itself wich lets a user
configure their own private settings for the door.

The meaning of DoorConfig is an easy way for the user to configure
configurable doors installed. Normally doors which have config possibilities
have to be started with argument '-w' or 'w', but not every door.
There is no guide line for this.

FAME DoorConfig doors can be entered here and can then be easy accessed
by the user via using the "W" command where users can configure everything
of the BBS. It's "W 14" (DOOR CONFIG) where the user can see the list of
installed DoorConfig doors and start them.

FAME DoorConfig is a FAME only thing and there can be only used FAME only
doors as DoorConfig doors, but you can also start other doors like XIM
ones etc. with a special FAME DoorConfig door (FAMEDoorConfig.FIM) which
is a FAME door and will start a DoorConfig door installed as a normal
SYSCMD door.

For more informations about this see the ReadMe.txt file in FAMEDoC1.lha
pack file.

             @{"     Door Config Name    " link "SEDoCoDoorConfigName"} @{"            NR           " link "SEDoCoNR"}
             @{"     Door Config Path    " link "SEDoCoDoorConfigPath"} @{"            NC           " link "SEDoCoNC"}
             @{"        Arguments        " link "SEDoCoArguments"} @{"            CF           " link "SEDoCoCF"}
             @{"         Password        " link "SEDoCoPassword"} @{"            SR           " link "SEDoCoSR"}
             @{"       Access Level      " link "SEDoCoAccessLevel"} @{"            SC           " link "SEDoCoSC"}
             @{"        Stack Size       " link "SEDoCoStackSize"} @{"            AR           " link "SEDoCoAR"}
             @{"         Priority        " link "SEDoCoPriority"} @{"            AC           " link "SEDoCoAC"}
             @{"           TOP           " link "SEDoCoTOP"} @{"            RD           " link "SEDoCoRD"}
             @{"          BOTTOM         " link "SEDoCoBOTTOM"} @{"          UNUSED         " link "SEDoCoUNUSED"}
             @{"     Listview Gadget     " link "SEDoCoListviewGadget"} @{"            UP           " link "SEDoCoUP"}
             @{"           DOWN          " link "SEDoCoDOWN"}

             @{"           SAVE          " link "SEDoCoSAVE"} @{"           NEW           " link "SEDoCoNEW"}
             @{"          DELETE         " link "SEDoCoDELETE"} @{"           BACK          " link "SEDoCoBACK"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoDoorConfigName" "Door Config Name"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Door Config Name:
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The DoorConfig door name displayed in the listview gadget and in the Node's
list on using "W 14" (DOOR CONFIG).

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoDoorConfigPath" "Door Config Path"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Door Config Path:
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The path to the DoorConfig door (FIM only door) or to the FAMEDoorConfig.FIM
door which starts foreign non-FIM doors for configuring them.

Normally located in 'FAME:Modules/DoorConfig/<The DoorConfig door>'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoArguments" "Arguments"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Arguments:
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Arguments for the DoorConfig door.

If the installed door is not a special DoorConfig door which doesn't need
arguments left this empty.

If it's the same door as the door for which you can configure datas, but
arguments are needed to inform the door about opening in config mode, type
here the needed arguments. Example: 'w' or '-w'.

If you use a foreign non-FIM door with FAMEDoorConfig.FIM type here the name
of the as SYSCMD installed foreign door (also with arguments behind the name
if needed).

For more informations about this see the ReadMe.txt file in FAMEDoC1.lha
pack file.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoPassword" "Password"


                      @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Password:
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

A password the user must type in correctly before the DoorConfig door will
be started.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoAccessLevel" "Access Level"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Access Level:
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The level a user must have to start this DoorConfig door.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoStackSize" "Stack Size"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Stack Size:
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The stack size for the DoorConfig door.

Some doors are needing more than 4096 bytes stack, here you can raise the
stack. Look in the document of the door to see how much stack it needs.

Default is 0 and means the System will give the door a stack of 4096 bytes
as default.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoCoPriority" "Priority"


                      @{b}SystemEditor (Door Config) Priority:
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The priority a DoorConfig door should run with.

Default is 0 and this is normally the best priority you should always use.

@endnode

