@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEDoorsUserHandler" "User Handler"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Doors): User Handler
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

                            @{fg shine}NOT IMPLEMENTED YET !!!@{fg text}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can enter CLI based tools which will be executed if something
important happens to a user data entry like:

 - Deleting a user.
 - Entering a new user/newuser (append/replace).
 - Renaming a user.
 - Inactivating a user.
 - Re-activating a user.

The idea behind this is to combine this with DoorConfig FIME doors to inform
them so they can update parallel their user configs.

                            @{fg shine}NOT IMPLEMENTED YET !!!@{fg text}

                              @{" User Handler Name " link "SEUsCoUserHandlerName"}
                              @{" User Handler Path " link "SEUsCoUserHandlerPath"}
                              @{"     Stack Size    " link "SEUsCoStackSize"}
                              @{"      Priority     " link "SEUsCoPriority"}

                              @{"        NEW        " link "SEUsCoNEW"}
                              @{"        SAVE       " link "SEUsCoSAVE"}
                              @{"       DELETE      " link "SEUsCoDELETE"}
                              @{"        BACK       " link "SEUsCoBACK"}

@endnode

