@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEUsCoStackSize" "Stack Size"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (User Handler) Stack Size:
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The stack size for the User Handler.

Some User Handlers are maybe needing more than 4096 bytes stack, here you can
raise the stack. Look in the document of the User Handler to see how much
stack it needs.

Default is 0 and means the System will give the User Handler a stack of
4096 bytes as default.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEUsCoPriority" "Priority"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (User Handler) Priority:
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

The priority a User Handler should run with.

Default is 0 and this is normally the best priority you should always use.

@endnode

