@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure global screens.

Screens are text files which will be viewed on special positions in the node.

             @{" Private.txt Min NumLin. " link "SEScreensPrivateMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlPrivate"}
             @{" Title.txt Min NumLines  " link "SEScreensTitleMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlTitle"}
             @{" Logon.txt Min NumLines  " link "SEScreensLogonMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlLogon"}
             @{"  Bull.txt Min NumLines  " link "SEScreensBullMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlBull"}
             @{" JoinConf.txt Min NumLi. " link "SEScreensJoinConfMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlJoinConf"}
             @{" NewUserPW.txt Min Nu.L. " link "SEScreensNewUserPWMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlNewUserPW"}
             @{"  Logoff.txt Min NumLi.  " link "SEScreensLogoffMinNumL"} @{"     Min Break Level     " link "SEScreensMinBrkLvlLogoff"}
             @{"    Show Private.txt     " link "SEScreensShowPrivate"} @{"     Show Title.txt      " link "SEScreensShowTitle"}
             @{"     Show Logon.txt      " link "SEScreensShowLogon"} @{"      Show Bull.txt      " link "SEScreensShowBull"}
             @{"    Show JoinConf.txt    " link "SEScreensShowJoinConf"} @{"   Show NewUserPW.txt    " link "SEScreensShowNewUserPW"}
             @{"     Show Logoff.txt     " link "SEScreensShowLogoff"}

