@REM==============================================================================

@node "FileCheckers" "File Checkers"


                         @{b}SystemEditor: File Checkers
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure filecheckers.

Filecheckers are needed to check the uploaded files for errors.

                          @{"        Checker         " link "SEFileChkChecker"}
                          @{"    Extension (.#?)     " link "SEFileChkExtension"}
                          @{" Other Extension (.#?)  " link "SEFileChkOtherExt"}
                          @{"          NEW           " link "SEFileChkNEW"}
                          @{"      Checker Path      " link "SEFileChkCheckerPath"}
                          @{"       Stack Size       " link "SEFileChkStackSize"}
                          @{"        Priority        " link "SEFileChkPriority"}
                          @{"        Options         " link "SEFileChkOptions"}
                          @{"      Error 1 - 5       " link "SEFileChkError1to5"}
                          @{"    FileId Extractor    " link "SEFileChkFileId Extractor"}
                          @{"    FidEx Stack Size    " link "SEFileChkFidExStackSize"}

                          @{"          SAVE          " link "SEFileChkSAVE"}
                          @{"          BACK          " link "SEFileChkBACK"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkChecker" "Checker"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Checker
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable the current checker.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkExtension" "Extension (.#?)"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Extension (.#?)
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Select between different known filetypes (checkers).

Note: Select or Cycle! means select via file-requester a filetype (checker)
      from disk or cycle with this gadget to a known checker.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkOtherExt" "Other Extension (.#?)"


              @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Other Extension (.#?)
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Use the popup gadget to select a filetype/checker/extension via
file-requester.

The string gadget is only usable if you have klicked on @{"NEW" link "SEFileChkNEW"} to generate a
new filetype/checker/extension.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkNEW" "NEW"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): NEW
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Generate a completely new filetype/checker/extension.
If you use this gadget the gadget @{"Other Extension (.#?)" link "SEFileChkOtherExt"} will be usable.
Type here the extendion of the new filetype/checker.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkCheckerPath" "Checker Path"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Checker Path
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the full path to the filechecker which shall be used for the
current filetype/extension.

You can also use the popup gadget to select the filechecker via
file-requester.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkStackSize" "Stack Size"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Stack Size
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the stack size needed be the filechecker for the current
filetype/extension.

Note: See the documents of the filechecker you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkPriority" "Priority"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Priority
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the priority which shall be used by the filechecker for the
current filetype/extension.

Note: Default is -1, because most filecheckers will take too much CPU
      resources. On a higher priority it may interrupt your BBS.
      -1 is totally enough especially for background checking.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkOptions" "Options"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Options
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the options needed by the filechecker to test the file of the
current filetype/extension.

Note: See the documents of the filechecker you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkError1to5" "Error 1 - 5"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): Error 1 - 5
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here up to 5 possible error message strings produced by the
filechecker, used for the current filetype/extension, if they find errors
in a file/archive.

Note: See the documents of the filechecker you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkFileId Extractor" "FileId Extractor"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): FileId Extractor
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the full path to the filechecker/packer/FileIdExtractor tool
you use to extract the file 'FILE_ID.DIZ' out of a file/archive.

Those tools will need options and the source file + the output path.
Use the keywords '%F' and '%W' (%F=From File %W=Work Path) to build the
needed options string you have to place after the full path to the
used tool.

Example for LHA: 'LHA -q e %F FILE_ID.DIZ %W'
Example for LZX: 'LZX -a x %F FILE_ID.DIZ %W'
Example for DMS: 'DMSDescript x %WFILE_ID.DIZ %F'
Example for EXE: 'EXEDescript x %WFILE_ID.DIZ %F'
Example for TXT: 'TXTEXTRACT e %WFILE_ID.DIZ %F'

Note: The file created must be located in the same Node as the uploaded
      file, but in the Work directory and must have the name 'FILE_ID.DIZ'.
      '%W' will be the path to the Work directory of the same Node.
      '%F' is the full path to the Playpen directory of the Node + filename.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkFidExStackSize" "FidEx Stack Size"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): FidEx Stack Size
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here the stack size needed be the filechecker/packer/FileIdExtractor
tool for the current filetype/extension.

Note: See the documents of the tool you use for details.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkSAVE" "SAVE"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): SAVE
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Save the File Checkers settings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEFileChkBACK" "BACK"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (File Checkers): BACK
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Cancel this window and go back into the main window of the SystemEditor.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "TextLanguage" "Text Language"


                         @{b}SystemEditor: Text Language
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure text file languages.

There are the text language types needed for locale and the extensions
for text files which can be viewed in different languages.

                           @{" Text Lang. Type 1 - 15 " link "SETextLangType1to15"}
                           @{"    Extension 1 - 15    " link "SETextLangExt1to15"}

                           @{"          SAVE          " link "SETextLangSAVE"}
                           @{"         CANCEL         " link "SETextLangCANCEL"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SETextLangType1to15" "Text Lang. Type 1 - 15"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Text Language): Text Lang. Type 1 - 15
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here 1 to 15 different languages.
The languages will be used for user-locale.


Examples and the first time from the SystemEditor generated:

 1: english
 2: deutsch
 3: dansk
 4: espańol
 5: français
 6: italiano
 7: nederlands
 8: norsk
 9: portuguęs
10: svenska
11:


Note: The first free gadget indicates the end of the Text Lang. Types.
      In this case 11 is free so FAME uses Text Lang. Types from 1 to 10.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SETextLangExt1to15" "Extension 1 - 15"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Text Language): Extension 1 - 15
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Type here 1 to 15 different Extensions.
The Extensions will be used for textfile Extensions to have textfiles in
different languages/ansis.


Examples and the first time from the SystemEditor generated:

 1: TXT
 2: GER
 3: DAN
 4: ESP
 5: FRA
 6: ITA
 7: NDL
 8: NOR
 9: POR
10: SVE
11:


Note: The first free gadget indicates the end of the Extensions.
      In this case 11 is free so FAME uses Extensions from 1 to 10.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SETextLangSAVE" "SAVE"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Text Language): SAVE
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Save the Text Language settings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SETextLangCANCEL" "CANCEL"


                      @{b}SystemEditor (Text Language): CANCEL
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Cancel this window and go back into the main window of the SystemEditor.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ExtXferMods" "Ext Xfer Mods"


                          @{b}SystemEditor: Ext Xfer Mods
                         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure external transfer modules like FAMEHydra and
FAMESModem.

                       @{"     Write (Hydra) Logfile      " link "SEExtXfrModWriteHydLog"}
                       @{"   Remember Window positions    " link "SEExtXfrModRemWndPos"}

                       @{"       Def. PublicScreen        " link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"}
                       @{"        Other PubScreen         " link "SEExtXfrModOtherPubScr"}
                       @{"       FallBack PubScreen       " link "SEExtXfrModFallBPubScr"}
                       @{"     Write (SModem) Logfile     " link "SEExtXfrModWriteSMdmLog"}
                       @{"           Auto Exit            " link "SEExtXfrModAutoExit"}
                       @{"          Remote Yell           " link "SEExtXfrModRemoteYell"}
                       @{"         Check Carrier          " link "SEExtXfrModChkCarrier"}
                       @{"            RTS/CTS             " link "SEExtXfrModRTSCTS"}
                       @{"         Encapsulation          " link "SEExtXfrModEncaps"}
                       @{"   Upload on normal Download    " link "SEExtXfrModUlonnormDl"}
                       @{"    Upload on Door Download     " link "SEExtXfrModUlonDoorDl"}
                       @{"   Upload on Message Download   " link "SEExtXfrModUlonMsgDl"}
                       @{"     Upload on ASL Download     " link "SEExtXfrModUlonASLDl"}
                       @{" Remote Auto Download (BEWARE!) " link "SEExtXfrModRemoteADl"}

                       @{"              SAVE              " link "SEExtXfrModSAVE"}
                       @{"             CANCEL             " link "SEExtXfrModCANCEL"}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModWriteHydLog" "Write (Hydra) Logfile"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Write (Hydra) Logfile
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable log writings into file 'FAME:Node<x>/Hydra.Log'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModRemWndPos" "Remember Window positions"


            @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Remember Window positions
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{"FAMEHydra" link "FAMEHydra.guide/Main"} will be able to remember every window position and size if you
change them while @{"FAMEHydra" link "FAMEHydra.guide/Main"} is running.

@{"FAMEHydra" link "FAMEHydra.guide/Main"} remembers the positions and sizes Node depended.

To get the origin positions and sizes back delete the file
'FAME:Settings/Node<x>/FAMEHydra.dat'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr" "Def. PublicScreen"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Def. PublicScreen
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

You can choose between four different public screen types:

 - FAME Node Public Screen   for the Node<x> screen.
 - SModem Public Screen      for SModem's own screen.
 - Workbench Public Screen   for the workbench screen.
 - FrontMost Public Screen   for the frontmost public screen.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModOtherPubScr" "Other PubScreen"


                 @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Other PubScreen
                ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can define a completely from @{"Def. PublicScreen" link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"} different
public screen.

This will disable gadget @{"Def. PublicScreen" link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModFallBPubScr" "FallBack PubScreen"


                @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): FallBack PubScreen
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Here you can define a fallback public screen.

This screen will be used if the screen defined with @{"Def. PublicScreen" link "SEExtXfrModDefPubScr"}
or @{"Other PubScreen" link "SEExtXfrModOtherPubScr"} is not available or can't be locked.

Note: If no screen is available or can't be locked including the fallback
      public screen, FAMESModem will try to lock your computers default
      public screen. If this failes too FAMESModem tries to lock the
      workbench.
      At the very last FAMESModem gives up and lets SModem open it's own
      screen.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModWriteSMdmLog" "Write (SModem) Logfile"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Write (SModem) Logfile
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable log writings into file 'FAME:Node<x>/FAMESModem.Log'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModAutoExit" "Auto Exit"


                    @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Auto Exit
                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Exit after transfer has completed.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModRemoteYell" "Remote Yell"


                   @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Remote Yell
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable remote page.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModChkCarrier" "Check Carrier"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Check Carrier
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable carrier checking (Enable is recommended).

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModRTSCTS" "RTS/CTS"


                     @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): RTS/CTS
                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable CTS/RTS handshaking (Enable is recommended).

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModEncaps" "Encapsulation"


                  @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Encapsulation
                 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable force encapsulation.

Use this for eg. Telnet connections.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModUlonnormDl" "Upload on normal Download"


            @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Upload on normal Download
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable uploading of files during a normal download.

Note: This should be always on else bi-directional transfers makes no sense.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModUlonDoorDl" "Upload on Door Download"


             @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Upload on Door Download
            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable uploading of files during a download out of a door.

Note: This should normally be off, because the door must be able to handle
      also uploaded files and which door does it ?
      Uploaded files will be deleted.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModUlonMsgDl" "Upload on Message Download"


            @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Upload on Message Download
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable uploading of files during a download of files over a mail.

Note: This should be always off, because the message base don't know what to
      do with the uploaded files and they will be deleted.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModUlonASLDl" "Upload on ASL Download"


              @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Upload on ASL Download
             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Enable/Disable uploading of files during a download started via
ASL-Requester.

Note: This should be always off, because ASL-Requester downloads has to
      be started by the sysop and has nothing to do with a normal upload.
      Uploaded files will be deleted.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModRemoteADl" "Remote Auto Download (BEWARE!)"


          @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): Remote Auto Download (BEWARE!)
         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Allow/Forbid remote end to add stuff from your disk to the batch.

Note: Be careful with this, because you lose control of what a user is
      downloading and what not.

      This should be always off !

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModSAVE" "SAVE"


                       @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): SAVE
                      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Save the Ext Xfer Mods settings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SEExtXfrModCANCEL" "CANCEL"


                      @{b}SystemEditor (Ext Xfer Mods): CANCEL
                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

Cancel this window and go back into the main window of the SystemEditor.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "uNuSED" "uNuSED"


                             @{b}SystemEditor: uNuSED
                            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

This window is no longer available.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "FAMEModules" "FAME Modules"


                          @{b}SystemEditor: FAME Modules
                         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Here you can configure the locations of FAME modules.

FAME modules are executables and an important part of FAME.

                            @{"   Server Location    " link "SEFAMEModsServerLoc"}
                            @{"  MainPart Location   " link "SEFAMEModsMainPartLoc"}
                            @{"  SystemEd Location   " link "SEFAMEModsSystemEdLoc"}
                            @{"   UserEd Location    " link "SEFAMEModsUserEdLoc"}
                            @{"    Info Location     " link "SEFAMEModsInfoLoc"}
